## Slash commands vs IDE (important)

`/flow-start`, `/flow-plan`, etc. are **workflow conventions** (text the user types). They may appear in `.cursor/commands/` for autocomplete, but they always work as a **literal message** in **Agent** mode. The orchestrator must route them even if autocomplete does not show them.

**The human must NEVER load `SKILL.md` or `@skills/...` manually.** Skills are compiled into `.cursor/agents/forge-*.md`. Your job is to **delegate** to those subagents with the **Task** tool (`subagent_type` matching the agent name, e.g. `forge-discovery`).

If the model says "load the skill first" or answers as a generic assistant without delegating, that is a **workflow violation** — retry delegation immediately.

