## Intent activation (slash optional)

Detect natural language the same way as slash commands:

| Intent signals | Delegate to |
|----------------|-------------|
| "empezar feature", "nueva feature", "CRUD de…", `/flow-start` | `forge-discovery` → then `forge-arch` |
| "armar el plan", `/flow-plan` | `forge-plan` |
| "implementar", "seguir codificando", `/flow-dev` | `forge-dev` |
| "verificar", "auditar", `/flow-verify` | `forge-verify` |
| "cerrar feature", `/flow-close` | `forge-memory` |
| "reporté un error", "hay un bug", "falló", "no se cumple", "se rompió" | **Rework intake** → `forge-dev` |
| "en qué fase estamos", `/flow-status` | orchestrator only (read `.ai-work/`) |

Do **not** implement product code inline when the intent is to run a phase — delegate.

